{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862123148,"sessionID":"ses_28660ebcdffe4WXFwNvaCbpCyj","part":{"id":"prt_d79a18a0e001IAMF6c3U46LGnS","messageID":"msg_d799f678b001tQaDdS3m7i6YYu","sessionID":"ses_28660ebcdffe4WXFwNvaCbpCyj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ba6e67f785694132873d798c90b6c88b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/agentd`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify pkg/agentd directory structure\n- [ ] Verify pkg/agentd directory exists\n- [ ] Create pkg/agentd directory if missing\n- [ ] Verify controller.go exists\n- [ ] Verify controller_test.go exists\n- [ ] Verify constants.go exists\n- [ ] Verify metrics.go exists (optional)\n\n**Verification**: Run `ls -la pkg/agentd/` and verify all required files exist\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Verify constants.go defines required constants\n- [ ] Verify SessionExpirationTimeout constant is defined (15 * time.Minute)\n- [ ] Verify LastActivityAnnotationKey constant is defined (\"last-activity-time\")\n- [ ] Verify DefaultRequeueInterval constant is defined (30 * time.Second)\n- [ ] Verify time package is imported\n- [ ] Verify constants have proper documentation comments\n- [ ] Verify constant values match design specifications\n\n**Verification**: Review constants.go implementation and verify all constants are correctly defined\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Verify Reconciler struct definition in controller.go\n- [ ] Verify Reconciler struct embeds client.Client\n- [ ] Verify Reconciler struct has Scheme field (*runtime.Scheme)\n- [ ] Verify client package is imported from sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\n- [ ] Verify runtime package is imported from k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\n- [ ] Verify reconciler package imports are correct\n- [ ] Verify struct has proper documentation comments\n\n**Verification**: Review controller.go and verify Reconciler struct matches design\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Implement Reconcile method - Get sandbox resource\n- [ ] Verify Reconcile method signature matches controller-runtime Reconciler interface\n- [ ] Verify context parameter is accepted\n- [ ] Verify req reconcile.Request parameter is accepted\n- [ ] Verify agentsv1alpha1.Sandbox is instantiated\n- [ ] Verify r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox) is called\n- [ ] Verify apierrors.IsNotFound(err) check is implemented\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{}, nil is returned for NotFound errors\n- [ ] Verify err is returned for other errors\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping with context\n\n**Verification**: Test Reconcile method with non-existent sandbox resource\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Implement Reconcile method - Read and validate annotation\n- [ ] Verify sandbox.Annotations is accessed\n- [ ] Verify LastActivityAnnotationKey is used to lookup annotation\n- [ ] Verify exists check is implemented for annotation\n- [ ] Verify empty string check is implemented\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{}, nil is returned for missing/empty annotation\n- [ ] Verify annotation value is extracted correctly\n\n**Verification**: Test Reconcile method with sandbox without last-activity-time annotation\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Implement Reconcile method - Parse last activity time\n- [ ] Verify time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr) is called\n- [ ] Verify parsing error is handled\n- [ ] Verify error message includes context (\"failed to parse last activity time\")\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: DefaultRequeueInterval} is returned on error\n- [ ] Verify error is wrapped with fmt.Errorf and %w\n- [ ] Verify lastActivity time variable is stored for later use\n\n**Verification**: Test Reconcile method with invalid RFC3339 time format\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Implement Reconcile method - Calculate expiration time\n- [ ] Verify SessionExpirationTimeout constant is used\n- [ ] Verify expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout) is calculated\n- [ ] Verify time.Now().After(expirationTime) check is implemented\n- [ ] Verify time.Until(expirationTime) is calculated for RequeueAfter\n\n**Verification**: Review time calculation logic and verify timeout matches 15 minutes\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement Reconcile method - Delete expired sandbox\n- [ ] Verify r.Delete(ctx, sandbox) is called for expired resources\n- [ ] Verify apierrors.IsNotFound(err) check is implemented for delete error\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{}, nil is returned if resource not found\n- [ ] Verify err is returned for other delete errors\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{}, nil is returned on successful delete\n- [ ] Verify proper error wrapping for delete failures\n\n**Verification**: Test Reconcile method with sandbox that has expired (>15 minutes idle)\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement Reconcile method - Requeue for non-expired sandbox\n- [ ] Verify time.Until(expirationTime) is calculated\n- [ ] Verify reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)} is returned\n- [ ] Verify nil is returned as error\n- [ ] Verify RequeueAfter duration is positive\n- [ ] Verify RequeueAfter is not zero or negative\n\n**Verification**: Test Reconcile method with active sandbox (<15 minutes idle) and verify RequeueAfter time\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Implement SetupWithManager method\n- [ ] Verify SetupWithManager method signature matches controller-runtime interface\n- [ ] Verify mgr ctrl.Manager parameter is accepted\n- [ ] Verify ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr) is called\n- [ ] Verify For(&agentsv1alpha1.Sandbox{}) is configured\n- [ ] Verify Complete(r) is called\n- [ ] Verify error is returned if setup fails\n- [ ] Verify method watches only Sandbox resources\n\n**Verification**: Review SetupWithManager implementation and verify controller registration\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Add logging to Reconcile method\n- [ ] Verify klog package is imported\n- [ ] Verify InfoS log is added when sandbox is deleted due to inactivity\n- [ ] Verify log includes namespace, name, and idleDuration\n- [ ] Verify ErrorS log is added for delete failures\n- [ ] Verify log includes context (namespace, name, error)\n- [ ] Verify log messages follow Kubernetes logging conventions\n\n**Verification**: Review logging statements and verify proper context is included\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Create cmd/agentd directory and main.go\n- [ ] Verify cmd/agentd directory exists\n- [ ] Create cmd/agentd directory if missing\n- [ ] Verify main.go exists\n- [ ] Verify main package is declared\n- [ ] Verify proper imports are present (controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox, agentd)\n\n**Verification**: Run `ls -la cmd/agentd/` and verify main.go exists\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Implement main.go - Scheme initialization\n- [ ] Verify runtime.NewScheme() is called\n- [ ] Verify clientgoscheme.AddToScheme(scheme) is called\n- [ ] Verify agentsv1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme) is called\n- [ ] Verify utilruntime.Must is used for error handling\n- [ ] Verify scheme is defined as package-level variable\n- [ ] Verify proper imports for scheme packages\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./cmd/agentd` and verify scheme initialization compiles\n\n---\n\n### Task 14: Implement main.go - Command line flags\n- [ ] Verify metricsAddr flag is defined (default: \":8080\")\n- [ ] Verify probeAddr flag is defined (default: \":8081\")\n- [ ] Verify enableLeaderElection flag is defined (default: false)\n- [ ] Verify zap.Options are configured\n- [ ] Verify opts.BindFlags(flag.CommandLine) is called\n- [ ] Verify flag.Parse() is called\n- [ ] Verify proper flag help text\n\n**Verification**: Run `./cmd/agentd --help` and verify flags are displayed\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Implement main.go - Manager initialization\n- [ ] Verify ctrl.NewManager is called with ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()\n- [ ] Verify Scheme is set to scheme variable\n- [ ] Verify MetricsBindAddress is set from flags\n- [ ] Verify Port is set to 9443\n- [ ] Verify HealthProbeBindAddress is set from flags\n